-- Romania’s Dafora Wins $13 Million Water System Upgrade Contract
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-10-29T07:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-29/romania-s-dafora-wins-13-million-water-system-upgrade-contract.html
Romania ’s  Dafora SA (DAFR) , together with
Italy’s Construzioni Dondi S.p.A, won a contract to upgrade the
water system in the Alba county, the company said in a statement
to the Bucharest Stock Exchange.  The value of the contract for the upgrade in the county,
located in central Romania, is about 46 million lei ($13
million) and will be financed from European Union funds, Dafora
said in the statement.  The two companies will upgrade and expand the water and
wastewater systems in the towns of Cugir, Campeni, Petresti,
Sebes and Sebesel in about 24 months, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
